text: Wilmington is the largest city in the state of Delaware, United States, and the county seat of New Castle County. It had 70,898 people in 2020. Wilmington has an area of about and is above sea level, at the place where the Christina River and Brandywine Creek meet. U.S. President Joe Biden is from Wilmington and owns a home here. ==Surrounding municipalities== ==References== Category:County seats in Delaware Category:1638 establishments in the Thirteen Colonies Category:17th-century establishments in Delaware
